cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC

This paper deals with network neutrality and its implications on pricing and revenue generation for service and content providers. The paper also considers the impact of side-payments and discrimination by access providers. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves game theory and cooperative/non-cooperative scenarios, which suggests the possibility of it being categorized under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also discusses security and privacy concerns, which could place it under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves information theory and pricing models, which could categorize it under cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of non-monopolistic content providers, which could place it under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
